Description: 1964 Silvertone Teisco TG1 Electric Guitar Vintage 1964/65 Silvertone TG-1 (aka model 1487) manufactured by Teisco Del Ray of Japan for Sears was the first guitar to have a built in amplifier! The amp provided 1/2 watt output to a 4 inch speaker. Models sold by Teisco had dual cutaway, came in different colors & hardware configurations. Models branded for Sears were single cutaway & chocolate brown in color. Appears to have had a short run of 1 year based on available information. These are quite rare & usually the amp is not working. The one depicted here with its brushed metal pick-guard is missing the battery pack and backplate, and the volume knob is cracked. Since the battery pack is missing, I do not know for certain if the built in amp works or not. Original Silvertone strap included as pictured. I do not have the original case, but it will ship securely in a gig bag, and sturdy guitar box. For a 50+ year old guitar, overall it is in pretty decent shape, and could make a great restoration project for collectors.Please look over pictures carefully for more details of condition.This guitar will ship FREE AND INSURED!Kentucky residents pay 6% sales tax.
